v0.1.4.1
  -	To avoid any "case sensitivity" issues, I tweaked TITLE so that it is all
	lowercase letters when the function is searching the string to see if it
	contains "kali" or "ubuntu" in the name.

v0.1.4
  -	Renamed startbar.py to "startbar"
  -	Modified the script's permission and made it an executable file

v0.1.3.2
  -	Tweaked the default coloring used for Kali distros


v0.1.3
  -	Changed default BG color to 196 if the distro is neither Ubuntu or Kali
	  -	If Kali, the default BG color will be 51 (cyan - Kali's color scheme)
	  -	if Ubuntu, the default BG color will be 202 (orange - Ubuntu's color scheme)
	  -	If the '-b' option is used, the BG color will be over written with the option
		used.


v0.1.2
  -	Changed default BG color to 202

